<question-stem>
<para> What does the professor mean when he says:<mediaExhibit frameType="mp3"
mediaRef="toeflPrac10213_02.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> That he is returning to his original topic after
an interruption</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> That he wants to find out what the students know</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> That he is summarizing the argument so far</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> That he is unsure what is being asked</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> "So ... what about the music?" means that the professor wants to explore
the earlier topic of music further (A). This is a rhetorical question; therefore,
he is not trying to discover (find out) or elicit his students' responses
(B). <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> So </emphasis>here does not mean <emphasis
emphasis-type="italic"> therefore </emphasis>or <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> to</emphasis><emphasis
emphasis-type="italic"> summarize </emphasis>(C). The professor's tone is
confident, rather than unsure of his topic (D).</para>
</explanation>
</question>
